<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870310-0084 </DOCNO><HL> Technology DevelopmentStake of 5.3% Is Disclosed</HL><DD> 03/10/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TDCXTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Leon Greenblatt, a Chicago investor, said he has a 5.3% stake in Technology Development Corp.'s common shares outstanding.    In a Securities and Exchange Commission filing, Mr. Greenblatt said he holds 89,450 Technology Development common shares for investment purposes. The stake includes 6,400 shares purchased in the last 60 days at $3 to $3.50 each.    In Arlington, Texas, a Technology Development spokeswoman said Mr. Greenblatt had long been an investor in the supplier of testing equipment. &quot;We haven't had any communication with this gentleman or that company to indicate there'd be anything more to (Mr. Greenblatt's ownership) than just for an investment.&quot;    In Chicago, Mr. Greenblatt couldn't be reached for comment. </TEXT></DOC>